{"title":"Macworld readers debate the best and worst Apple products of all time","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/342347/macworld-readers-debate-the-best-and-worst-apple-products-of-all-time.html","date":1617528600000,"content":"<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd\">\n<html><body><div id=\"link_wrapped_content\">\n<section class=\"wp-block-bigbite-multi-title\"><div class=\"container\"></div></section><p>Apple&rsquo;s 45th anniversary was on April 1 but the company isn&rsquo;t much into celebrating such occasions. They didn&rsquo;t do anything major publicly, though there was a tweet from CEO Tim Cook (who also sent a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://appleinsider.com/articles/21/04/01/tim-cook-reflects-on-45-years-of-apple-in-company-wide-email&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">message to Apple employees</a>).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">As Apple celebrates 45 years today, I&rsquo;m reminded of Steve&rsquo;s words from many years ago: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s been an amazing journey so far, yet we have barely begun.&rdquo; Thanks to every member of our Apple family for all you&rsquo;ve done to enrich lives. Here&rsquo;s to the next 45 years &amp; beyond!</p>&mdash; Tim Cook (@tim_cook) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/tim_cook/status/1377622693261021184?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><p>Here at Macworld, we took the opportunity to look back at Apple&rsquo;s product history and pick our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.macworld.co.uk/feature/best-apple-products-of-all-time-3803292/\">best</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/342225/worst-apple-products-of-all-time.html\">worst</a> products from the company. And of course, our dear readers had their own thoughts on these lists, agreeing with some of our choices, but also eager to point out where we went wrong. So here is a compilation of some of the responses we received on Twitter and Facebook.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"sock-it-to-us\">Sock it to us</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We, um, <em>really</em> weren&rsquo;t expecting all the love readers have for the iPod Socks. The list did post on April Fool&rsquo;s day, so maybe the joke was on us? I still remember the day Steve Jobs&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/1040629/ipodsocks.html\">introduced</a>&nbsp;the iPod Socks at an event in 2004, when, sandwiched between media members, we looked at each other, befuddled.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">The socks were amazing &ndash; I loved my iPod socks &#129392;</p>&mdash; Cinnamon Rage &#127793; (@CinnamonRage) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/CinnamonRage/status/1377658617642516486?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-worst-socks-rleahy.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Facebook iPod Socks\" class=\"wp-image-100060711\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-worst-socks-pscoble.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Facebook iPod Socks\" class=\"wp-image-100060712\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-worst-socks-birving.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Facebook iPod Socks\" class=\"wp-image-100060713\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"high-praise-for-the-hi-fi\">High praise for the Hi-Fi</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We included the iPod Hi-Fi on our worst list, and many of you were ready to come to its defense. Yes, the iPod Hi-Fi produced good sound (which I didn&rsquo;t actually say in the list writeup), but I did point out that it didn&rsquo;t sound as good as some of its competitors. (And @delabaviere, I&nbsp;<em>do</em>&nbsp;have the iPad Hi-Fi. The picture in the article is of my very own.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Ipod HiFi was amazing. HOW DARE YOU</p>&mdash; Musklon Eel (@musklon_eel) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/musklon_eel/status/1378031190695936001?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 2, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Sorry but iPod Hi-Fi was and is still is a brilliant device.</p>&mdash; Jonny (@Tilneys) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Tilneys/status/1377749542163132417?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Replace the iPod Hi-Fi with the G4 cube and it would really fit well</p>&mdash; mineTurtle DXR &#63743; (@mineTurtleDXR) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/mineTurtleDXR/status/1377842371753295880?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 2, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">The author apparently never had the iPod Hi-Fi. I still have it, best sound!</p>&mdash; M (@delabaviere) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/delabaviere/status/1377698505251295234?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><h2 id=\"what-da-puck\">What da puck?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Longtime Apple users are in almost unanimous agreement that the Apple USB Mouse&mdash;a.k.a the hockey puck mouse&mdash;is a bad product. I said&nbsp;<em>almost</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I&rsquo;m one of the few who didn&rsquo;t mind the round puck mouse.</p>&mdash; Emoco (@emoco) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/emoco/status/1377680655774060551?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I love the puck mouse but it&rsquo;s cancer to use. Siri Remote I actually like though, besides how easy it is to lose.</p>&mdash; Brennont97 (@Brennont97) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Brennont97/status/1377687461988593672?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><p>Some thought the Magic Mouse deserved to be on the list.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Magic Mouse 2</p>&mdash; LukeWarm (@LkWarm) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/LkWarm/status/1377933976761987073?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 2, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-worst-magicmouse-hdwig.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Facebook Worst Apple Product\" class=\"wp-image-100060714\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-worst-fb-mbrown.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Facebook Worst Apple Product\" class=\"wp-image-100060715\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Oh yeah, that&nbsp;<em>was</em>&nbsp;good</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Our list of Apple&rsquo;s best products didn&rsquo;t garner as many responses are our worst list. Which, knowing how human nature works, was probably to be expected. But those of you who did respond had some great comments.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">The &ldquo;Sunflower&rdquo; iMac G4 was truly an incredible product. The design was not the most long lasting in Apple&rsquo;s lineup, but it was most certainly one of the best. The screen was incredibly thin compared to the competition too.</p>&mdash; AppleUser (@AppleUser2000) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/AppleUser2000/status/1377708256001458178?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I don&rsquo;t see an iPad. Apart from the iPhone and iPod, it is the most amazing piece of technology ever created. Imagine a portable computer you can carry with you in your brief case or purse anywhere in the world that&rsquo;s lightweight and efficient and works like a laptop? Amazing.</p>&mdash; EarlyRiser (@VeryEarlyRiser) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/VeryEarlyRiser/status/1377706109490843656?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><div class=\"extendedBlock-wrapper block-coreImage undefined\"><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/apple-best-tipb-demery.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1024\" alt=\"Apple Best Products\" class=\"wp-image-100060716\"></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159011411691544&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"imageCredit\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"hey-macworld-who-asked-you-anyway\">Hey Macworld, who asked you anyway?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">&ldquo;Happy anniversary!! This is what we hate about you!!&rdquo;<br>Imagine if that&rsquo;s how anniversaries actually went for humans lol</p>&mdash; tweeted: (@innovationsdead) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/innovationsdead/status/1377672296664551426?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">What a positive and uplifting approach to Apple&rsquo;s 45th birthday.</p>&mdash; J.P. Wing (@ThatGeekJPWing) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/ThatGeekJPWing/status/1377656558532751360?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure><p>Okay, so maybe there are better ways to celebrate Apple&rsquo;s 45th&nbsp;anniversary. Point taken. We&rsquo;ve got some time to work on something really good for the 50th anniversary. In the meantime, these words from @alextsayun are ones we&rsquo;ll keep in mind.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"500\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Without Apple you would not exist <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.1/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"🙂\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>&mdash; Alex Tsayun (@alextsayun) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/alextsayun/status/1377687442992533504?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-342347-0-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" rel=\"nofollow\">April 1, 2021</a></blockquote><script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></div></figure></div></body></html>","author":"Roman Loyola","siteTitle":"Google silicon could turn the Pixel into the iPhone biggest competitor","siteHash":"845b35ef5bc2ddfaa008518eedb9033f664423bfda890a9666e8caa95d6201be","entryHash":"780d85619afdda0361aeabee8a94ab0d332a4ae451a110d16f9b11bcd8175681","category":"Apple"}